<subSubSection id="1B94653CD65B9B00FF5BFD59FDDFFCD0" pageId="2" pageNumber="448" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="533136B7D65B9B00FF5BFD59FDDFFCD0" blockId="2.[151,1437,151,896]" pageId="2" pageNumber="448">
<emphasis id="61FAEAA5D65B9B00FF5BFD59FEF1FD07" bold="true" box="[199,315,655,680]" pageId="2" pageNumber="448">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="948E4D34D65B9B00FED4FD46FDF7FD08" authority="Monné &amp; Monné &amp; Botero, 2017" authorityName="Monné &amp; Monné &amp; Botero" authorityYear="2017" box="[328,573,656,680]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lophobothea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nearnsi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="61FAEAA5D65B9B00FED4FD46FDF7FD08" box="[328,573,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="448">Lophobothea nearnsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="7AC957DED65B9B00FDD6FD59FD60FD07" box="[586,682,655,680]" pageId="2" pageNumber="448" rank="species">
<emphasis id="61FAEAA5D65B9B00FDD6FD59FD60FD07" bold="true" box="[586,682,655,680]" pageId="2" pageNumber="448">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="948E4D34D65B9B00FCCAFD47FB5AFD07" authority="Bates, 1881" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1881" box="[854,1168,656,680]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Carneades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reticulata">
<emphasis id="61FAEAA5D65B9B00FCCAFD47FC2CFD07" box="[854,998,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="448">L. reticulata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="371F4B46D65B9B00FC67FD46FB42FD07" author="Bates" box="[1019,1160,656,680]" pageId="2" pageNumber="448" refString="Bates, H. W. (1881) New species of longicorn Coleoptera allied to Colobothea. The Entomologist's Monthly Magazine, 17, 275 - 277." type="journal article" year="1881">Bates, 1881</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in having the grayish pubescence of the elytra arranged as a net of irregular patches, each patch surrounded by brownish-black pubescence. It differs mainly in the pronotum with five longitudinal stripes of brownish-black pubescence, the central stripe wider than the others, the lateral tubercles of prothorax reduced to a minute protuberance, and the posterior row of punctures of the pronotum situated in a depressed area. In 
<taxonomicName id="948E4D34D65B9B00FC66FCF7FB4FFC97" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1881" box="[1018,1157,800,824]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Carneades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reticulata">
<emphasis id="61FAEAA5D65B9B00FC66FCF7FB4FFC97" box="[1018,1157,800,824]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="448">L. reticulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the median longitudinal line is divided, the lateral tubercle of the prothorax is more projected, and the posterior row of punctures of the pronotum is situated in a flat area.
</paragraph>
